                            <comment id="14463653" author="ait" created="Tue, 27 Nov 2007 04:01:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Jochen!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you please have a look. The problem is that ClosureMetaClass choose doCall of outer closure because inner one explicitly declares Date param type and instead of failing we choose doCall of parent. Probably for call and doCall we need to ignore delegates&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here is test case for your convenience&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;package&lt;/span&gt; groovy.bugs

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Groovy2339Bug &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;extends&lt;/span&gt; GroovyTestCase {

    void testBug () {
        List list = [&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;groovy&apos;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;java&apos;&lt;/span&gt;]

        Map map = [a: 1, b: 2]

        list.each {
            map.keySet().each {Date d -&amp;gt;
                println d
            }
        }
    }
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14463764" author="blackdrag" created="Tue, 27 Nov 2007 10:11:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fixed by not going to the delegate if a doCall/call method is called &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
